        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 11:29PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 1130 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 22
miles north of Clyde Park, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
The north half of the Crazy Mountain Range, Martinsdale and Lennep.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
